<DOC><DOCNO> AP880812-0030 </DOCNO><FILEID>AP-NR-08-12-88 0634EDT</FILEID><FIRST>r i PM-Philippines     08-12 0223</FIRST><SECOND>PM-Philippines,0229</SECOND><HEAD>Rebels Wound Troops, Damage Helicopters</HEAD><DATELINE>CEBU, Philippines (AP) </DATELINE><TEXT>   Communist rebels ambushed a militarypatrol on Negros island, wounding five soldiers, and damaged threehelicopters that were flying in reinforcements, the military saidtoday.   The military's Visayas Command said New People's Army guerrillasambushed the patrol Thursday near Guihulngan, 350 miles southeastof Manila.   Six helicopters were dispatched from nearby Bacolod withreinforcements but the rebels fired on the aircraft. Two of thehelicopters were forced to land at the scene but the third returnedto base with the wounded, the report said.   There was no report of rebel casualties. The wounded include thepatrol leader, Lt. Juanito Bero, and the gunner of one of thedamaged helicopters, the report said. It did not say what happenedto the helicopters and helicopter crews that were forced to land atthe scene of the battle.   A reporter for a Bacolod radio station, DYEZ, quoted soldiers assaying one civilian militiaman was also wounded and seven otherswere missing.   Civilian militiamen often accompany soldiers on patrols in rebelareas.   The military said it could not confirm that any militiamen weremissing because reports were sketchy.   The New People's Army, the armed wing of the Communist Party ofthe Philippines, has been waging an insurgency to establish aMarxist state for 19 years.</TEXT></DOC>